    "hc_tab_content_highlights_MqRhp3": {
      "type": "hc-tab-content-highlights",
      "blocks": {
        "self_cleaning_DaGVUw": {
          "type": "self-cleaning",
          "settings": {
            "tag": "01 — Biologically Clean",
            "heading": "SELF-CLEANING FABRIC?",
            "description": "<p>Yes, the Jax Sheets are woven with a permanent <strong>Silver Grid</strong> that continuously inhibits the growth of bacteria, fungi, and odor-causing microbes across the entire surface.<br/>Unlike conventional bedding that passively accumulates what your body sheds through the night, the silver ions are constantly active against the microbes that thrive in warm, humid bedding environments. This keeps the fabric genuinely cleaner between washes and makes it a more hygienic environment for your skin over the long term.</p>",
            "badge_text": "99.9% Bacteria Neutralized",
            "footer_text": "Anti-Microbial Barrier Analysis",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "tooltip_trigger": "Silver Grid",
            "tooltip_content": "<p><strong>What is it?</strong></p><p>A silver grid is a network of ultra-fine silver threads woven directly into the fabric at precise intervals, forming a continuous grid structure throughout the textile. Unlike silver ion treatments that are applied to the surface of a fabric and degrade with washing, a woven silver grid is a permanent part of the sheet's construction. It does not wash out, fade, or lose effectiveness over time.</p><p><strong>Why is it in the Jax Sheets?</strong></p><p>Silver is one of the most effective natural antimicrobial elements known, and in the Jax Sheets it works continuously to inhibit the growth of bacteria, fungi, and odor-causing microbes across the entire surface of the fabric. Because the silver is woven in rather than coated on, its protective properties remain consistent wash after wash and year after year. The result is a sheet that maintains a genuinely hygienic sleep surface over the long term, without relying on chemical treatments or needing to be replaced to stay effective.</p>",
            "bg_color": "#ffffff",
            "text_color": "#000000",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "desc_color": "#4b5563"
          }
        },
        "charcoal_ash_system_pxVJaK": {
          "type": "charcoal-ash-system",
          "settings": {
            "tag": "02 — ODOR DEFENSE & HUMIDITY CONTROL",
            "heading": "The Charcoal and Ash System",
            "description": "<p>To complement the silver's active protection, we've woven in <strong>Coconut Charcoal</strong> and <strong>Volcanic Ash</strong> to manage the environment of your bed. While the charcoal acts as a natural filter to trap and neutralize odors, the <strong>volcanic ash</strong> works to pull skin humidity away before it can turn into liquid sweat. By removing this moisture, the fabric denies bacteria the damp environment they need to multiply in the first place. This system keeps your bed dry and fresh for up to two months between washes.</p>",
            "architecture_title": "DEEP SLEEP ARCHITECTURE",
            "card_1_title": "Coconut Charcoal",
            "card_1_subtitle": "Odor Filter",
            "card_2_title": "Volcanic Ash",
            "card_2_subtitle": "Humidity Pull",
            "result_title": "Sweat Free Deep Sleep Zone",
            "badge_1": "Active 24/7",
            "badge_2": "Zero Odor",
            "reverse_layout": true,
            "tooltip_1_trigger": "Coconut Charcoal",
            "tooltip_1_content": "<p><strong>What is Coconut Charcoal?</strong></p><p>Coconut charcoal is a highly activated form of carbon derived from upcycled coconut shells. At a microscopic level it is defined by its extreme porosity, containing millions of tiny pores that create a massive internal surface area. This structural engineering allows it to function as a powerful molecular filter rather than a passive material.</p><p><strong>Why is it in the Jax Sheets?</strong></p><p>We use coconut charcoal because your bed accumulates organic impurities and high levels of humidity over every 8 hour sleep cycle. Its porous structure acts as a molecular magnet, adsorbing sweat and odors while rapidly pulling moisture away from your skin as it forms. By continuously managing skin humidity throughout the night, the charcoal helps prevent the damp, clammy feeling common with traditional bedding, creating a drier, fresher sleep environment that stays cleaner between washes regardless of the season.</p>",
            "tooltip_2_trigger": "Volcanic Ash",
            "tooltip_2_content": "<p><strong>WHAT IS VOLCANIC ASH?</strong></p><p>Volcanic ash consists of microscopic, mineral-rich particles formed during volcanic eruptions. In our textiles, this ash is refined into an ultra-fine, porous powder that is permanently embedded into the fiber. Unlike smooth synthetic fibers, these particles have a high surface area and a unique physical structure that makes them naturally effective at managing thermal energy and moisture.</p><p><strong>WHY IS IT IN JAX SHEETS?</strong></p><p>We use Volcanic Ash as a high-speed engine for moisture evaporation. While charcoal traps odors, the volcanic ash works to accelerate the movement of humidity away from your body. Its unique mineral structure increases the fabric's surface area, allowing it to pull moisture from your skin and disperse it across the fabric for near-instant evaporation. This prevents the \"heavy\" or \"soggy\" feel of traditional cotton, ensuring your bed remains dry and temperature-regulated even if you tend to sleep hot.</p>",
            "tooltip_3_trigger": "volcanic ash",
            "tooltip_3_content": "<p><strong>WHAT IS VOLCANIC ASH?</strong></p><p>Volcanic ash consists of microscopic, mineral-rich particles formed during volcanic eruptions. In our textiles, this ash is refined into an ultra-fine, porous powder that is permanently embedded into the fiber. Unlike smooth synthetic fibers, these particles have a high surface area and a unique physical structure that makes them naturally effective at managing thermal energy and moisture.</p><p><strong>WHY IS IT IN JAX SHEETS?</strong></p><p>We use Volcanic Ash as a high-speed engine for moisture evaporation. While charcoal traps odors, the volcanic ash works to accelerate the movement of humidity away from your body. Its unique mineral structure increases the fabric's surface area, allowing it to pull moisture from your skin and disperse it across the fabric for near-instant evaporation. This prevents the \"heavy\" or \"soggy\" feel of traditional cotton, ensuring your bed remains dry and temperature-regulated even if you tend to sleep hot.</p>",
            "bg_color": "#000000",
            "text_color": "#ffffff",
            "accent_color": "#b45309",
            "desc_color": "#9ca3af"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
